com.oracle.truffle.api.strings

Class AbstractTruffleString

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.oracle.truffle.api.strings.AbstractTruffleString
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MutableTruffleString, TruffleString

    public abstract class AbstractTruffleString
extends Object
    Abstract base class for Truffle strings. Useful when a value can be both a TruffleString or a MutableTruffleString. Note that values of this type are not valid interop values. They must be converted to TruffleString before passing them to other languages.
    Since:
    22.1
    See Also:
    TruffleString

      • isCompatibleToUncached

        public final boolean isCompatibleToUncached(TruffleString.Encoding expectedEncoding)
        Returns true if this string is compatible to the given encoding. Compatible for TruffleString means it is byte-equivalent in both the encoding used to create this string and the given encoding. For MutableTruffleString this method only returned true if the passed encoding is the same encoding used to create this string.
        Since:
        23.0
